<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880509-0058 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Sherwood Group Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WNEWS SHD WOFG </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Sherwood Group Inc. said it signed a letter of intent to sell 10 of its 33 retail brokerage offices to Wolf Financial Group Inc.Terms weren't disclosed.    The offices are primarily in the Southeast and in California.    Sherwood is a New York-based holding company. Its two units provide brokerage and investment services. Also in New York, Wolf is an investment banker and broker-dealer.    Separately, Sherwood's Phillip Siegel will adopt the post of chief operating officer. He currently is executive vice president and chief financial officer. </TEXT></DOC>